<tr >
	<td colspan=5><p><b><font face=Arial size=2>Detailed Description:</font></b></p></td>
</tr><tr>    
    <td colspan=5><font face=Arial size=1>THE RELEASE WAS THE RESULT OF A FAULTY CAMLOCK CONNECTION WHILE TRANSFERRING PRODUCED WATER TO THE STORAGE POND. BEST PROFESSIONAL JUDGEMENT INDICATES ~42.3 BBLS OF PRODUCED WATER WERE RELEASEDD DURING THIS INCIDENT. RELEASED PRODUCED WATER TRAVELED DOWN THE ACCESS ROAD ACROSS TO THE MAIN ROAD AT THE BOTTOM OF THE POND AND SETTLED IN AN IRRIGATION DITCH ON THE OPPOSITE SIDE OF THE ACCESS ROAD. THE IRRIGATION DITCH WAS NOT IN USE (DRY). ALL STANDING WATER WAS REMOVED AND IMPACTED SOIL REMOVAL IS CURRENTLY UNDERWAY.</font></td>
</tr>

